What is Packet Sniffing?

Imagine standing beside a highway and observing vehicles passing by.

Each vehicle = a network packet
Vehicle type = protocol (TCP/UDP/ICMP)
License plate = IP address
Goods inside vehicle = payload/data

A packet sniffer works similarly. It listens to network traffic and displays information about packets traveling through the network.

Real Example

When your browser opens a website:

Your computer sends packets to the website server
The packets contain:
Source IP
Destination IP
Protocol type
Data being transmitted

The sniffer captures and displays these details.

